Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) Healthwatch helps operators understand the current health, performance, and capacity of a given PCF foundation. It stores and visualizes recommended key operational metrics from core PCF components, including BOSH-reported VM metrics, as well as creates additional measures of operational value based on continuous validation tests and contextually derived metrics.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

PCF Healthwatch includes the following key features:

* Offers an opinionated PCF Operational Monitoring dashboard, providing coverage of the recommended [Key Performance Indicators](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/monitoring/kpi.html) and [Key Scaling Indications](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/monitoring/key-cap-scaling.html) for a given version of PCF. Associated data is retained for 25 hours.
* Executes recommended operational health checks as continuous validation tests. It stores and displays the results of the checks as well as [forwards](using.html#firehose) this data into the [Loggregator Firehose](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/loggregator/architecture.html#firehose) for external consumption by existing customer solutions.

